Ever since I had first watched this episode of the final seventh season of the 2003 TV series, I had often wondered why the writers and animators had the Turtles relocate to a different lair instead of having them still living in the third lair that they had them living in throughout the rest of season 4, season 5, the beginning of the first episode of season 6 and the end of the first episode of season 7. Donnie still would've had the extra space to build the cyber-portal.

https://c1.staticflickr.com/3156/2892084417_250f9a11e9_b.jpg

Khan is reminiscent of another character called Tatsu, who was introduced for the first and second live-action Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles films that were released in theaters on March 30th of 1990 and March 22nd of 1991 and reintroduced for the episode "The Forgotten Swordsman" of the final fifth season of the 2012 Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles computer-animated TV series that was first aired on Nickelodeon on March 26th of 2017.

As much as I enjoyed watching the final seventh season myself, I would've preferred reintroducing Khan as Tatsu instead, because if you think about it, they're really not all that different from each other, except for their appearance, but their personalities are quite similar since they were both loyal to the Shredder and had intentions to rebuild the Foot. Plus, it would've been epic if the 2003 TV series also had it's own version of Tatsu. So, why not have him go by that name instead? I don't see any reason why not. Ever since then, I had wondered why the people who worked for 4Kids Entertainment didn't just go along with that.
